@DATABASE "ppmtoilbm.guide"
@INDEX "ImageEditor.guide/INDEX"
@FONT helvetica.font 13
@SMARTWRAP

@NODE MAIN "ImageEditor - Saver: IFF [ppmtoilbm]"
@TOC "Saver.guide/MAIN"

@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}IFF@{UB}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}
@{PAR}@{B}Convert a portable pixmap into an IFF-Picture file.@{UB}@{LINE}
@{PAR}Reads a portable pixmap file as input. Produces IFF-ILBM as output.@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
@{B}Save Format@{UB}@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 12}
    @{FG HIGHLIGHT}TrueColor:@{FG TEXT} 24 Planes with 8-bit RGB Values, excl. Colormap.@{LINE}
@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Bitplanes:@{FG TEXT} Normal ILBM with 1-8 Planes, inc. Colormap.@{LINE}
@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Palette:@{FG TEXT} Colormap File with BMHD and CMAP Chunks only.@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
@{B}Compression Method@{UB}@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 12}
    Select compression method.
Compression requires building the ILBM image in memory;
turning compression off allows stream-writing of the image,
but the resulting file will usually be 30% to 50% larger.@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
@{B}Masking Method@{UB}@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 12}
    Select masking method. Method can be none (no masking,
default) or maskplane (only for Bitplane-ILBMs).
lasso masks are are not supported yet.@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
@{B}Use Maskfile@{UB}@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 12}
    Use a mask file to mark transparent pixels in an IFF- ILBM.
The Maskfile is a normal BITMAP image, the same size (or larger) as the input file.
A pixel value of WHITE in the mask file means the corresponding in the input file is considered to be transparent,
BLACK indicates an opaque pixel (think of the input file casting a shadow on a white screen).@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
@{B}Use Colormap@{UB}@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 12}
    Uses the colors found in the mapfile to create the colormap in the IFF file,
instead of the colors from ppmfile. The mapfile can be any ppm file;
all that matters is the colors in it. If the colors in ppmfile
do not match those in mapfile, they are matched to a "best match".@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 8}@{LINE}
@{B}Floyd Steinberg@{UB}@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 12}
    Use Floyd-Steinberg error diffusion for mapping the input colors to the colors in the mapfile.
The results are usually much better than without it, but it takes substantially more CPU time.@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}See also the @{" IFF " LINK "ilbmtoppm.guide/MAIN"} loader.@{LINE}
@{PAR}[@{B}ppmtoilbm@{UB}] @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{I}Copyright (C) 1994 by Ingo Wilken @{UI}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE
